	<LINE>ROBERTSON BEQUEST.</LINE>
	<LINE>Founded by Miss Isobel Robertson, 5th August,</LINE>
	<LINE>1844. The funds are to be distributed amongst (1)</LINE>
	<LINE>ten decayed gentlewomen, who shall have been re-</LINE>
	<LINE>siding for at least 10 years in Glasgow, who shall</LINE>
	<LINE>not be less than 45 years of age, and shall never</LINE>
	<LINE>have been married; (2) ten females each of whom</LINE>
	<LINE>shall have, for at least seven years consecutively,</LINE>
	<LINE>been a hired servant in one family in Glasgow, shall</LINE>
	<LINE>not be under 50 years of age, shall never have been</LINE>
	<LINE>married, and at the time of selection shall be out of</LINE>
	<LINE>service. Amount of Pensions at present (1) £9,</LINE>
	<LINE>and (2) £4 10s.</LINE>
	<LINE>Factor, J. Roxburgh Strong, C.A,, 110 West</LINE>
	<LINE>George st.</LINE>
	<LINE>GLASGOW ORKNEY AND SHETLAND</LINE>
	<LINE>BENEVOLENT SOCIETY.</LINE>
	<LINE>Instituted January 11, 1837.</LINE>
	<LINE>Bailie Wm. Walls, president ; Thos. Stout, James</LINE>
	<LINE>D. Marwick, vice-presidents ; John Ireland, Frederick</LINE>
	<LINE>Anderson, D. W. Sinclair, J. G. C. Cheyne, David D.</LINE>
	<LINE>Leisk, John Riddoch, Henry Leask, David Work, and</LINE>
	<LINE>David Garriock, directors; T. Stout, jun., 178 St.</LINE>
	<LINE>Vincent St., treasurer ; S. S. Eunson, 13 Dixon St.,</LINE>
	<LINE>secretary.</LINE>
	<LINE>The principal object of the society is to grant</LINE>
	<LINE>charitable relief to the natives of the Orkney and</LINE>
	<LINE>Shetland islands, their children, or widows, residing</LINE>
	<LINE>in Glasgow or its neighbourhood, or travelling through</LINE>
	<LINE>Glasgow, and who, from sickness or sudden emer-</LINE>
	<LINE>gency, may be in want of temporary aid. No</LINE>
	<LINE>applicant shall be relieved whose character for</LINE>
	<LINE>honesty, sobriety, and industry has not been satis-</LINE>
	<LINE>factorily ascertained.</LINE>
